com.hyperwallet.android.model.graphql.keyed

Class MappedConnection<T extends com.hyperwallet.android.model.graphql.keyed.KeyedNode>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hyperwallet.android.model.graphql.Connection<T>
      • com.hyperwallet.android.model.graphql.keyed.MappedConnection<T>

  • public class MappedConnection<T extends com.hyperwallet.android.model.graphql.keyed.KeyedNode>
extends Connection<T>
    Represents a Connection/Edges of a Node that can also be reference by a key, this means that the MappedConnection edges will have the ability to reference a Node through by a specific key assigned to a Node.

    To make the MappedConnection effective the Node itself must be keyed so that we will know the identity of that Node when placed in the graph.

    MappedConnection is derived from Connection that means iterating a connection without using keys is also possible
